# Clinora Patient Management Product Requirements Document

**Product:** Clinora
**Module:** Patient Management
**Document Type:** Product Requirements Document
**Version:** 1.0
**Status:** Draft
**Prepared By:** Product Management and Engineering
**Audience:** Product, UI/UX, Frontend, Backend, QA, DevOps and Architecture Teams

---

## 1. Purpose

The purpose of this document is to define the business, functional, security, data, user-interface and technical requirements for the Patient Management module of Clinora.

The Patient Management module provides the central patient record used throughout the Clinora platform. It allows authorized clinic users to register, search, view and update patients while allowing patients to manage selected portions of their own profiles.

This module serves as the foundation for:

* Appointment booking
* Consultation and electronic medical records
* Prescriptions
* Laboratory orders and reports
* Billing and payments
* Patient communication
* Follow-up care
* Reporting and analytics

---

## 2. Business Objective

The objective of the Patient Management module is to provide every clinic with a secure, accurate and centralized patient record.

The module should reduce duplicate registration, manual data entry and fragmented patient information while enabling doctors and clinic staff to access the information required for patient care and daily operations.

The module must also support Clinora’s multi-tenant SaaS architecture by ensuring that one clinic cannot access another clinic’s patient data.

---

## 3. Scope

### 3.1 Included in MVP

The MVP will include:

* Patient self-registration
* Patient registration by reception staff
* Patient registration by clinic administrators
* Patient search
* Patient profile
* Patient demographic information
* Contact information
* Emergency contact
* Basic medical information
* Allergies
* Existing medical conditions
* Patient status
* Patient appointment history
* Patient consultation history
* Prescription list
* Laboratory report list
* Invoice and payment history
* Patient timeline
* Patient document upload
* Profile updates
* Duplicate patient detection
* Tenant isolation
* Audit logging

### 3.2 Out of Scope for MVP

The following items are planned for later releases:

* Family-account management
* Dependents and guardian accounts
* Cross-clinic medical-record sharing
* National health identification integration
* Ayushman Bharat Digital Mission integration
* Insurance-policy management
* Patient-consent management for external sharing
* Patient record merge workflow
* Data import from external EMR systems
* Mobile biometric identification
* Advanced clinical coding
* AI-generated patient summaries
* Voice-based patient search

---

## 4. Actors

| Actor                | Description                                                                    |
| -------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------ |
| Patient              | Registers, views and updates selected personal information                     |
| Reception Staff      | Registers and searches patients for appointments and billing                   |
| Doctor               | Views assigned or authorized patient information and clinical history          |
| Laboratory Staff     | Views limited patient information required for lab processing                  |
| Clinic Administrator | Manages patient records within the clinic                                      |
| Clinora Super Admin  | Manages the platform but does not normally access clinical records             |
| System               | Performs validation, duplicate detection, audit logging and tenant enforcement |

---

## 5. User Personas and Needs

### 5.1 Patient

The patient needs to:

* Register quickly
* Avoid entering the same information repeatedly
* View personal details
* View appointments
* Access prescriptions
* Access lab reports
* View invoices and payments
* Update permitted profile fields

### 5.2 Reception Staff

Reception staff need to:

* Search patients quickly
* Identify existing patients
* Register new patients during phone, walk-in or online bookings
* Update contact details
* View appointment and payment information
* Avoid duplicate registrations

### 5.3 Doctor

The doctor needs to:

* Find a patient
* View relevant demographics
* View allergies and medical conditions
* View past consultations
* View prescriptions
* View lab reports
* View a complete patient timeline

### 5.4 Laboratory Staff

Laboratory staff need to:

* Identify the correct patient
* View lab orders
* Verify patient information
* Upload reports
* Avoid access to unnecessary clinical or financial data

### 5.5 Clinic Administrator

The clinic administrator needs to:

* View and manage patient records within the clinic
* Review patient growth
* Manage inactive patient records
* Export permitted operational information
* Review audit history where authorized

---

## 6. User Stories

### US-PAT-001: Patient Self-Registration

As a patient, I want to create my account so that I can book appointments and access my healthcare records.

### US-PAT-002: Staff Patient Registration

As a receptionist, I want to register a patient so that I can book an appointment on the patient’s behalf.

### US-PAT-003: Patient Search

As a receptionist or doctor, I want to search for a patient using name, mobile number or patient number so that I can quickly access the correct patient record.

### US-PAT-004: Patient Profile

As an authorized clinic user, I want to view a patient profile so that I can confirm demographic and contact information.

### US-PAT-005: Update Patient Information

As an authorized user, I want to update permitted patient information so that records remain accurate.

### US-PAT-006: Patient Timeline

As a doctor, I want to view the patient’s complete clinical timeline so that I can understand previous care before starting a consultation.

### US-PAT-007: Duplicate Detection

As a receptionist, I want the system to warn me when a similar patient already exists so that I do not create duplicate records.

### US-PAT-008: Patient Documents

As an authorized user, I want to upload supporting documents so that relevant records are available digitally.

### US-PAT-009: Patient Status Management

As a clinic administrator, I want to activate or deactivate a patient record so that unused or invalid profiles are managed appropriately.

### US-PAT-010: Patient Self-Service Profile Update

As a patient, I want to update my contact details so that the clinic can communicate with me correctly.

---

## 7. End-to-End Patient Registration Flow

### 7.1 Patient Self-Registration

```text
Patient opens clinic website
        ↓
Selects Register
        ↓
Enters mobile number or email
        ↓
Completes verification
        ↓
Enters profile information
        ↓
System validates duplicate records
        ↓
Patient account created
        ↓
Patient dashboard displayed
```

### 7.2 Reception Registration

```text
Reception opens Patient Search
        ↓
Searches mobile number or name
        ↓
Patient found?
   ┌───────────────┐
   │ Yes           │ No
   ↓               ↓
Open existing    Create new patient
patient          record
   │               │
   └───────┬───────┘
           ↓
Continue appointment booking
```

### 7.3 Patient Search and Profile Access

```text
Authorized user searches patient
        ↓
System validates clinic and role
        ↓
Search results returned
        ↓
User selects patient
        ↓
Patient profile and permitted information displayed
```

---

## 8. Functional Requirements

### FR-PAT-001: Create Patient

The system shall allow authorized users to create a patient record.

Required fields for MVP:

* First name
* Last name, where applicable
* Mobile number
* Date of birth or age
* Gender
* Clinic identifier
* Registration source
* Consent acknowledgement where required

Optional fields:

* Email
* Blood group
* Address
* Emergency contact
* Preferred language
* Marital status
* Occupation
* Identification document
* Referral source

### FR-PAT-002: Generate Patient Number

The system shall generate a unique patient number within the clinic.

Example:

```text
CLN-2026-000145
```

The patient number must:

* Be unique within the clinic
* Be immutable after creation
* Be suitable for display on receipts, prescriptions and reports

### FR-PAT-003: Search Patient

The system shall support patient search using:

* Patient number
* Mobile number
* Email
* First name
* Last name
* Full name
* Date of birth
* Partial name
* Appointment reference

Search results shall be tenant-filtered and permission-filtered.

### FR-PAT-004: View Patient Profile

The patient profile shall display permitted information including:

* Patient number
* Name
* Age and date of birth
* Gender
* Mobile number
* Email
* Address
* Emergency contact
* Blood group
* Allergies
* Medical conditions
* Recent appointment
* Upcoming appointment
* Latest prescription
* Latest lab report
* Payment status summary

### FR-PAT-005: Update Patient Profile

Authorized users may update permitted profile fields.

The system shall:

* Validate changed values
* Record old and new values
* Record who made the change
* Record the timestamp
* Prevent unauthorized changes to protected fields

### FR-PAT-006: Duplicate Detection

Before creating a patient, the system shall check for possible duplicates using:

* Mobile number
* Email
* Full name and date of birth
* Full name and gender
* Government identifier, if collected in future

When a potential duplicate is found, the system shall:

* Display matching profiles
* Allow the user to open the existing record
* Require confirmation before creating a new record
* Log an override when a new record is created despite a match

### FR-PAT-007: Patient Timeline

The system shall provide a chronological patient timeline containing permitted events such as:

* Registration
* Appointments
* Check-ins
* Consultations
* Diagnoses
* Prescriptions
* Lab orders
* Lab reports
* Invoices
* Payments
* Refunds
* Follow-up recommendations
* Uploaded documents

The timeline shall support filtering by:

* Date range
* Event type
* Doctor
* Appointment
* Clinical or financial category

### FR-PAT-008: Patient History

The system shall display patient history in organized sections:

* Appointment history
* Consultation history
* Prescription history
* Lab-order history
* Lab-report history
* Invoice history
* Payment history

### FR-PAT-009: Patient Documents

Authorized users shall be able to upload documents such as:

* Previous prescriptions
* External lab reports
* Referral letters
* Identification documents
* Insurance documents in future

The system shall store:

* Document type
* File name
* Secure object-storage reference
* Uploading user
* Upload date
* Clinic ID
* Patient ID
* Description
* Document status

### FR-PAT-010: Patient Status

Supported patient statuses:

```text
ACTIVE
INACTIVE
DECEASED
DUPLICATE_SUSPECTED
ARCHIVED
```

Status changes must:

* Require appropriate permission
* Be audited
* Not permanently delete clinical records

### FR-PAT-011: Patient Self-Service

Patients shall be able to:

* View their own profile
* Update mobile number after verification
* Update email after verification
* Update address
* Update preferred language
* Update emergency contact
* View appointments
* View prescriptions
* View lab reports
* View invoices and payments

Patients shall not be able to directly modify:

* Clinical notes
* Diagnoses
* Prescriptions
* Lab results
* Payment-confirmation status
* Doctor-entered medical history

### FR-PAT-012: Patient Consent

The system shall capture basic consent acknowledgement for:

* Platform use
* Communication notifications
* Medical-record processing
* Terms and privacy-policy acceptance

More advanced consent workflows will be introduced in future releases.

---

## 9. Business Rules

### BR-PAT-001

Every patient record must belong to one clinic in the MVP.

### BR-PAT-002

Every patient record must contain a valid clinic identifier.

### BR-PAT-003

A patient must not access another patient’s information.

### BR-PAT-004

Clinic users must not access patients from another clinic.

### BR-PAT-005

A mobile number may be unique within a clinic, subject to approved family-account rules in future.

### BR-PAT-006

A patient number must be unique within a clinic.

### BR-PAT-007

Patient clinical records must not be permanently deleted through normal application functions.

### BR-PAT-008

Patient demographic changes must be audited.

### BR-PAT-009

The frontend must not provide or override the clinic identifier for protected operations.

### BR-PAT-010

The backend shall derive clinic context from the authenticated session or token.

### BR-PAT-011

Doctors may view patient clinical history only when authorized by clinic policy and assigned access rules.

### BR-PAT-012

Laboratory staff shall receive only the minimum information required to process laboratory work.

---

## 10. Role-Based Access

| Capability               | Super Admin |    Clinic Admin | Reception |   Doctor |             Lab |            Patient |
| ------------------------ | ----------: | --------------: | --------: | -------: | --------------: | -----------------: |
| Create patient           |          No |             Yes |       Yes | Optional |              No |               Self |
| Search patients          |          No |             Yes |       Yes |      Yes |         Limited |               Self |
| View demographics        |  Restricted |             Yes |       Yes |      Yes |         Limited |               Self |
| Edit demographics        |          No |             Yes |       Yes |  Limited |              No |            Limited |
| View clinical history    |          No |    Policy-based |   Limited |      Yes |              No | Own shared records |
| View prescriptions       |          No |    Policy-based |   Limited |      Yes |              No |                Own |
| View lab reports         |          No |    Policy-based |   Limited |      Yes | Relevant orders |                Own |
| View payments            |          No |             Yes |       Yes |  Limited |              No |                Own |
| Upload patient documents |          No |             Yes |       Yes |      Yes |         Limited |             Future |
| Change patient status    |          No |             Yes |   Limited |       No |              No |                 No |
| Export patient data      |          No | Authorized only |        No |       No |              No |  Own future export |

