## 12. API Requirements

### 12.1 Create Patient

```http
POST /api/v1/patients
```

Example request:

```json
{
  "firstName": "Ravi",
  "lastName": "Kumar",
  "dateOfBirth": "1991-05-10",
  "gender": "MALE",
  "mobile": "9876543210",
  "email": "ravi@example.com",
  "registrationSource": "RECEPTION",
  "preferredLanguage": "en"
}
```

### 12.2 Search Patients

```http
GET /api/v1/patients?search=Ravi&page=0&size=20
```

### 12.3 Get Patient

```http
GET /api/v1/patients/{patientId}
```

### 12.4 Update Patient

```http
PATCH /api/v1/patients/{patientId}
```

### 12.5 Get Patient Timeline

```http
GET /api/v1/patients/{patientId}/timeline
```

### 12.6 Get Patient Appointments

```http
GET /api/v1/patients/{patientId}/appointments
```

### 12.7 Get Patient Prescriptions

```http
GET /api/v1/patients/{patientId}/prescriptions
```

### 12.8 Get Patient Lab Reports

```http
GET /api/v1/patients/{patientId}/lab-reports
```

### 12.9 Upload Patient Document

```http
POST /api/v1/patients/{patientId}/documents
```

### 12.10 Update Patient Status

```http
PATCH /api/v1/patients/{patientId}/status
```

---

## 13. Standard API Error Cases

| Error Code                | Description                               |
| ------------------------- | ----------------------------------------- |
| PATIENT_NOT_FOUND         | Patient does not exist or is inaccessible |
| PATIENT_DUPLICATE_FOUND   | A possible duplicate record exists        |
| PATIENT_NUMBER_CONFLICT   | Generated patient number is not unique    |
| MOBILE_ALREADY_REGISTERED | Mobile number is already registered       |
| EMAIL_ALREADY_REGISTERED  | Email is already registered               |
| PATIENT_ACCESS_DENIED     | User does not have permission             |
| INVALID_PATIENT_STATUS    | Requested status transition is invalid    |
| PATIENT_VALIDATION_FAILED | Submitted data is invalid                 |
| TENANT_ACCESS_DENIED      | User attempted cross-clinic access        |
| DOCUMENT_UPLOAD_FAILED    | Patient document could not be uploaded    |

